commit 93fac7b29900d27baec1e8552f746b453b0b1549
Author: phoenixborn17 <phoenixborn17@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Jul 6 00:05:17 2026 +0530

    @
    polish-1: require EMAIL_UNSUBSCRIBE_SECRET in production (Tier-B · SECURITY)
    
    Removes the silent DATABASE_URL/empty-string fallback for the unsubscribe HMAC
    key. Prod now: env validation flags it at boot + unsubscribeKey() throws fast if
    unset; dev still derives from DATABASE_URL so a laptop boots. No hardcoded secret
    (Golden Rule 5). Tests: prod-boot-without-secret flags/throws; dev derives.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    @

